kpi_info.title: DC_HSUPA_UE_SUM
kpi_info.use: Master HSUPA L2 shall determine the number of DC-HSUPA configured users and sample with 100ms period and sum the values to SUM counter. UPDATED: The number of DC HSUPA configured users are sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter

kpi_info.title: MAX_DC_HSUPA_USERS
kpi_info.use: Master HSUPA L2 shall estimate maximum value of concurrent DC HSUPA configured users, out of all samples during measurement period timestamp and update the value to this counter. UPDATED: The number of DC HSUPA configured users are sampled with 100 ms period and MAX value of all samples during measurement period are updated to this counter

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DCHSUPA_USERS_2C_SUM
kpi_info.use: Master HSUPA L2 shall determine the number of DC-HSUPA capable users using both primary as well as secondary carrier and sample with 100ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is reset when the next measurement interval starts. UPDATED: The number of DC HSUPA capable users using both primary as well as secondary carrier are sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is reset when the next measurement interval starts.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DCHSUPA_USERS_1C_SUM
kpi_info.use: Master HSUPA L2 shall estimate number of DC HSUPA capable users using only one carrier (primary), and sample with 100ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is reset when the next measurement interval starts. UPDATED: The number of DC HSUPA capable users using only one carrier (primary) are sampled with 100 ms period and summed to this counter. The counter is reset when the next measurement interval starts.

kpi_info.title: PIC_ACTIVE
kpi_info.use: Number of samples for monitoring relative time of PIC active state. UPDATED: Counter is incremented by one on each 100ms if cell PIC state is active.

kpi_info.title: PIC_INACTIVE
kpi_info.use: Number of samples for monitoring relative time of PIC inactive state. UPDATED: Counter is incremented by one on each 100ms if cell PIC state is inactive

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_PROMO_DL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI promotions in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is higher than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as promotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in promotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEMOT_DL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI demotions in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is lower than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as demotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter incremented by one when SPI change results in demotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEF_DL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of times the SPI is returned to its default value in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is equal to the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered by this counter. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter is incremented when SPI change results in SPI returning to its default value.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_PROMO_UL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI promotions in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is higher than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as promotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in promotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEMOT_UL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI demotions in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is lower than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as demotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in demotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEF_UL_AAR
kpi_info.use: Number of times the SPI is returned to its default value in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is equal to the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered by this counter. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented when SPI change results in SPI returning to its default value.
